The paper proposes an advanced deep learning framework for predicting traffic flow on a motorway using spatial and temporal features extracted from a large amount of data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of convolutional neural networks (CNN) and recurrent neural networks (RNN) indicates that the paper may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on traffic management and prediction suggests that it may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
